re></div><ul><li><p><strong>- Last year ONDC also took baby steps to enabling &#8216;skill-based services&#8217; on the network.</strong> Services make up <a href="https://pib.gov.in/PressReleasePage.aspx?PRID=1793804">50% of our GDP</a>, so it makes sense that any &#8216;commercial&#8217; network would be incomplete without accounting for the training, development and employment of our human capital. <br>- It means that in theory you could use ONDC to find a repairman or massage therapist (similar to how you&#8217;d use a platform like UrbanClap); or someone in rural India could find educational courses offered by edtech players live on the network; and that same person could also get a scholarship to complete that training by a company looking to fill its vacancies on the same network.</p></li></ul><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3672fe54-c676-43cd-bdd2-64b963f80168_800x532.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3672fe54-c676-43cd-bdd2-64b963f80168_800x532.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3672fe54-c676-43cd-bdd2-64b963f80168_800x532.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3672fe54-c676-43cd-bdd2-64b963f80168_800x532.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3672fe54-c676-43cd-bdd2-64b963f80168_800x532.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3672fe54-c676-43cd-bdd2-64b963f80168_800x532.jpeg" width="800" height="532" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/3672fe54-c676-43cd-bdd2-64b963f80168_800x532.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:532,&quot;width&quot;:800,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;ONEST&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;ONEST&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="ONEST" title="ONEST" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3672fe54-c676-43cd-bdd2-64b963f80168_800x532.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3672fe54-c676-43cd-bdd2-64b963f80168_800x532.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3672fe54-c676-43cd-bdd2-64b963f80168_800x532.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3672fe54-c676-43cd-bdd2-64b963f80168_800x532.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Illustrating the reach of the Open Network for Education and Skilling Transactions (ONEST), also built on Beckn like ONDC (Source: <a href="https://yourstory.com/2023/07/onest-ondc-beckn-decentralised-network-education-skilling-jobs">Yourstory</a>)</figcaption></figure></div><p>Beckn hopes to conjure marketplaces in every kind of avatar, helping to play matchmaker in any situation where demand is in courtship of supply (and vice versa). The flexibility and malleability of the Beckn protocol opens the door to many fascinating future commercial possibilities, especially if/when different Beckn-enabled ecosystems start to cross-pollinate. That&#8217;s why it&#8217;s worth paying close attention to the present experiences, suggestions, and complaints of ONDC&#8217;s first wave of settlers.</p><h2>Okay so what&#8217;s the experience actually been like for buyers?</h2><p>Much like a potato, there&#8217;s different ways to cut this (sorry). </p><p>The good news is that ONDC works. </p><p>You can log into familiar apps like PayTM, Meesho, MagicPin, or Pincode (by PhonePe) that have integrated with ONDC, and shop for listed items the same way you would with any other non-ONDC marketplace.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0d274c81-64f3-49e8-a47b-38640d9a55cf_2127x1125.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0d274c81-64f3-49e8-a47b-38640d9a55cf_2127x1125.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0d274c81-64f3-49e8-a47b-38640d9a55cf_2127x1125.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0d274c81-64f3-49e8-a47b-38640d9a55cf_2127x1125.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0d274c81-64f3-49e8-a47b-38640d9a55cf_2127x1125.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_2400,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0d274c81-64f3-49e8-a47b-38640d9a55cf_2127x1125.png" width="1200" height="634.6153846153846" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/0d274c81-64f3-49e8-a47b-38640d9a55cf_2127x1125.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:false,&quot;imageSize&quot;:&quot;large&quot;,&quot;height&quot;:770,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:1200,&quot;bytes&quot;:1283713,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-large" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0d274c81-64f3-49e8-a47b-38640d9a55cf_2127x1125.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0d274c81-64f3-49e8-a47b-38640d9a55cf_2127x1125.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0d274c81-64f3-49e8-a47b-38640d9a55cf_2127x1125.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0d274c81-64f3-49e8-a47b-38640d9a55cf_2127x1125.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">(1) PayTM is <a href="https://www.livemint.com/companies/news/paytm-eyes-to-bring-10-million-merchants-on-ondc-platform-in-next-two-years-vijay-shekhar-sharma-11701706537896.html">betting big </a>on ONDC, evidenced by the <a href="https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/technology/paytm-loves-ondc-gives-it-pride-of-place-on-homescreen-of-app-11816601.html">prime positioning</a> of the ONDC tab on the PayTM app; (2) PhonePe, one of the victors of the UPI race, took the approach of making a separate commerce app and front-end called Pincode; (3) Hyperlocal rewards and savings app MagicPin now lets its users make purchases and orders via ONDC (4) A screenshot from Namma Yatri, that&#8217;s emerged as a true challenge to Uber and Ola in Bangalore.</figcaption></figure></div><p>Or you can even download new apps like MyStore, which has been one of the early movers on the buyer app side of the equation. Because MyStore displays items from all the sellers that have been onboarded onto ONDC (via different seller apps), the selection of items on offer is more diverse (and perhaps more haphazard) that you&#8217;d normally be accustomed to.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8c20e6cb-4210-4a4f-ba50-c00c90fc08dc_2100x1118.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8c20e6cb-4210-4a4f-ba50-c00c90fc08dc_2100x1118.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8c20e6cb-4210-4a4f-ba50-c00c90fc08dc_2100x1118.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8c20e6cb-4210-4a4f-ba50-c00c90fc08dc_2100x1118.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8c20e6cb-4210-4a4f-ba50-c00c90fc08dc_2100x1118.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_2400,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8c20e6cb-4210-4a4f-ba50-c00c90fc08dc_2100x1118.png" width="1200" height="638.7362637362637" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/8c20e6cb-4210-4a4f-ba50-c00c90fc08dc_2100x1118.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:false,&quot;imageSize&quot;:&quot;large&quot;,&quot;height&quot;:775,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:1200,&quot;bytes&quot;:1349107,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-large" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8c20e6cb-4210-4a4f-ba50-c00c90fc08dc_2100x1118.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8c20e6cb-4210-4a4f-ba50-c00c90fc08dc_2100x1118.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8c20e6cb-4210-4a4f-ba50-c00c90fc08dc_2100x1118.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8c20e6cb-4210-4a4f-ba50-c00c90fc08dc_2100x1118.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">For those mornings when you wake up with the urge to eat a Big Mac in your saree</figcaption></figure></div><p>The interfaces used by each of these apps will be familiar to anyone that is a regular user of platforms like Amazon, BigBasket, Swiggy, and Uber. So it&#8217;s not that hard to start using ONDC. The bad news, is that for the digitally privileged, none of the current ONDC buyer apps really represent a step-function improvement on the e-commerce options currently at our disposal.</p><p>Because there&#8217;s so many more moving parts that have to be coordinated in the back end (independent buyer apps, seller apps, buyers, sellers, and logistics players), the ONDC user experience is a little clunkier and a little slower than what we&#8217;re used to. The trade off to swapping the tyranny of platforms for the egalitarianism of ONDC is that one company doesn&#8217;t have unilateral control over the value chain or the data passing through it. </p><p>So it&#8217;s not uncommon in this adolescent stage of ONDC to have cases where you can&#8217;t find a delivery agent after placing an order, or where the tracking is a little glitchy, or where you&#8217;ve ordered from a restaurant and while you&#8217;re at the check out stage you get an error-message saying the restaurant is closed or that the item you selected isn&#8217;t available. It then throws up the question about who takes the blame (and the economic hit for the failure). None of these issues are impossible to iron out (and they <em>are</em> being worked on), but it means that the current ONDC experience sits below the standard we expect for digital services in Tier-1 cities. </p><p>It poses the question about why someone in metropolitan India would bother buying things on ONDC right now. There are two main answers to this question:</p><ol><li><p>You can find a <strong>wider and more diverse selection of items</strong> that might not have already made it onto the shelves of any incumbent marketplace (for a variety of reasons). Eg: one of the leading seller apps on ONDC - called <a href="https://www.sellerapp.com/ondc.html">SellerApp</a> - has helped to onboard indigenous weavers from Kanchipuram so they can <a href="https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/ondc-partners-sellerapp-and-delhivery-drive-up-sales-for-kanjeevaram-weavers/article67442412.ece">generate orders</a> from any of the buyer apps that are live on the network, exposing them to the benefits of e-commerce for the first time.  </p></li></ol><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28d043a6-3090-43f5-b3f9-86122f6084ef_1131x1125.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28d043a6-3090-43f5-b3f9-86122f6084ef_1131x1125.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28d043a6-3090-43f5-b3f9-86122f6084ef_1131x1125.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28d043a6-3090-43f5-b3f9-86122f6084ef_1131x1125.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28d043a6-3090-43f5-b3f9-86122f6084ef_1131x1125.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28d043a6-3090-43f5-b3f9-86122f6084ef_1131x1125.png" width="474" height="471.48541114058355" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/28d043a6-3090-43f5-b3f9-86122f6084ef_1131x1125.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1125,&quot;width&quot;:1131,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:474,&quot;bytes&quot;:1195887,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28d043a6-3090-43f5-b3f9-86122f6084ef_1131x1125.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28d043a6-3090-43f5-b3f9-86122f6084ef_1131x1125.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28d043a6-3090-43f5-b3f9-86122f6084ef_1131x1125.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F28d043a6-3090-43f5-b3f9-86122f6084ef_1131x1125.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><ol start="2"><li><p>Prices for many items on ONDC are currently heavily discounted for final users owing to a <strong><a href="https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/business/startup/ondc-introduces-bonuses-of-up-to-rs-35-lakh-per-week-for-buyer-side-apps-ahead-of-festive-season-11468131.html">massive incentive programme</a></strong> being conducted by the ONDC organisation. This scheme has been in full throttle for <a href="https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/business/startup/ondc-launches-new-incentive-scheme-with-more-autonomy-for-buyer-apps-support-for-small-cities-11312051.html">most of last year</a>, helping to seed the network and nudge people into the habit of buying on ONDC. There are also offers and bonuses available for buyer apps, seller apps, and even logistics players to encourage more participation and activity across the ONDC value chain.</p></li></ol><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd6953a0b-6293-46c2-a398-8be2de52224c_1093x1125.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd6953a0b-6293-46c2-a398-8be2de52224c_1093x1125.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd6953a0b-6293-46c2-a398-8be2de52224c_1093x1125.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd6953a0b-6293-46c2-a398-8be2de52224c_1093x1125.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd6953a0b-6293-46c2-a398-8be2de52224c_1093x1125.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd6953a0b-6293-46c2-a398-8be2de52224c_1093x1125.png" width="628" height="646.3860933211345" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/d6953a0b-6293-46c2-a398-8be2de52224c_1093x1125.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1125,&quot;width&quot;:1093,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:628,&quot;bytes&quot;:335684,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd6953a0b-6293-46c2-a398-8be2de52224c_1093x1125.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd6953a0b-6293-46c2-a398-8be2de52224c_1093x1125.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd6953a0b-6293-46c2-a398-8be2de52224c_1093x1125.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd6953a0b-6293-46c2-a398-8be2de52224c_1093x1125.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Case in point, this is the difference in price for the same order of a veggie feast pizza from Pizza Hut on Swiggy vs PayTM (i.e. ONDC)</figcaption></figure></div><p>Right now there are only 13 live buyer apps on the network, but 73 more are in an advanced stage of development (including from banks and fintech companies, B2B platforms, FMCG companies, telecom players, mapping apps etc). The buying experience should become far more compelling once we start to see live buyer apps for specific geographies (eg: Tier-4 districts), specific sectors and products (eg: organic produce), specific form factors (eg: voice ordering), local dialects, and new functionalities (eg: AI-based smart shopping). </p><p>At the moment, the buyer experience is heavily dependant on the quality of sellers on the network, and particularly the level of experience of these sellers. Merchants that are new to e-commerce still have to learn the ropes. Vivek Lohcheb, the CEO of Pincode (one of the leading buyer apps on the network), articulated this challenge for me:</p><blockquote><p><em>&#8220;ONDC is &#8216;merchant-first&#8217; commerce, vs the product-first model of traditional e-commerce marketplaces. A customer is buying a Coke from ABC Stores, not from Pincode (or Amazon or Flipkart or Zomato). Their experience is shaped by how the seller fulfils their order. It is the responsibility of both buyer app and seller app to make sure a customer is satisfied. From our perspective as a buyer app - our promise is to offer customers the trust of an offline store with the convenience of an online store. </em></p><p><em>New sellers need to understand what it takes to cater to an online customers&#8217; needs. They cannot see the customer as someone else&#8217;s customer just because they are coming in via someone else&#8217;s app. These sellers need to think about their brand for the first time - they need to treat ONDC customers the same way they would treat a customer that walks into their store from the street. They need to think of the customer as walking into their digital store. It is their quality and their experience that will help the network scale. If we get this right, ONDC will be a success.</em></p></blockquote><p>This won&#8217;t happen overnight, and it speaks to the unique challenge of &#8216;open&#8217; commerce. Another one for the &#8216;time will tell&#8217; list.</p><h2>What about the seller experience?</h2><p>ONDC allows sellers to join the network in two ways - either by directly integrating with the network via their own self-managed storefront (referred to as &#8216;Inventory Seller Nodes&#8217;) or by onboarding via third party seller apps that play the role of &#8216;Marketplace Seller Nodes&#8217;. </p><p>Essentially, if you were a big DTC brand like <a href="https://retail.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/e-commerce/e-tailing/wearables-brand-boat-joins-ondc/99957336">BoAt</a> or a large FMCG company like <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/anjanikjajodia_kachuekichaal-tinydot-dpi-activity-7143662976560939008--LFd/">ITC</a>, you might want to invest the time, effort and money to go through the technical legwork of setting up shop on the network yourself - it would mean greater control over your operations and ultimately less fees paid to a third party. Alternatively, if your goal was to join the network and begin selling as fast as possible, you could register with any of the numerous existing seller apps that help merchants, retailers and brands to join ONDC with minimal effort.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F710a65b4-fdfd-4964-9fbc-7c71eaa5f6b4_1023x505.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F710a65b4-fdfd-4964-9fbc-7c71eaa5f6b4_1023x505.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F710a65b4-fdfd-4964-9fbc-7c71eaa5f6b4_1023x505.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F710a65b4-fdfd-4964-9fbc-7c71eaa5f6b4_1023x505.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F710a65b4-fdfd-4964-9fbc-7c71eaa5f6b4_1023x505.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F710a65b4-fdfd-4964-9fbc-7c71eaa5f6b4_1023x505.png" width="1023" height="505" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/710a65b4-fdfd-4964-9fbc-7c71eaa5f6b4_1023x505.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:505,&quot;width&quot;:1023,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:225710,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F710a65b4-fdfd-4964-9fbc-7c71eaa5f6b4_1023x505.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F710a65b4-fdfd-4964-9fbc-7c71eaa5f6b4_1023x505.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F710a65b4-fdfd-4964-9fbc-7c71eaa5f6b4_1023x505.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F710a65b4-fdfd-4964-9fbc-7c71eaa5f6b4_1023x505.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">(Not an exhaustive list of) Seller Apps live on ONDC</figcaption></figure></div><p>Some of these companies (eg: Bech, UniStack) have been newly formed to take advantage of the ONDC opportunity. However, most of these companies (like Gofrugal, Magicpin, and GrowthFalcons) have been around for a while, providing a range of digitisation and e-commerce enablement services for their SME clients, including things like inventory management, digital marketing, storefront management, POS systems, invoicing etc. The ability to integrate with ONDC via a few simple APIs makes it easy for them to offer &#8216;ONDC onboarding&#8217; as a service to their customers.</p><p>Seller apps help brands and merchants to start selling on ONDC. They guide them through the necessary registration and integration process. They help them digitise their catalogues as per the standard ONDC format (eg: names, images, descriptions etc). They provide inexperienced sellers with training on how to update their inventories and work with third party logistics services. Some seller apps even provide their sellers with network insights and data intelligence, and help them design discounts and promotional campaigns with popular buyer apps.</p><p>There&#8217;s also a number of specialist Technology Service Providers (TSPs) who provide the technical handholding to help larger companies join the network directly. TSPs essentially create smoother rails on top of the ONDC infrastructure that make it easy to deploy apps and solutions onto the network. <a href="https://plotch.ai/">Plotch.ai</a> and <a href="https://adya.ai/">Adya.ai</a> are leading ONDC TSPs that have each also completed a first round of venture funding led by <a href="https://entrackr.com/2023/07/plotch-ai-raises-pre-seed-funding-from-antler-peak-xv-others/">Antler India and Peak XV</a>, and by the <a href="https://ondc.org/blog/adya-ai-bags-funding-to-help-enterprises-build-apps-on-ondc/#:~:text=Enterprise%20tech%20startup%20Adya.ai,3.75%20Cr%20in%20the%20startup.">Indian Angel Network (IAN)</a> respectively. Between the two of them they&#8217;ve helped heavyweights like PayTM, IDFC, HUL, Canara Bank, Aditya Birla Group, and other enterprise clients to build on ONDC.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2c8d825a-e5e4-45bb-9703-652fb93fdc2a_903x131.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2c8d825a-e5e4-45bb-9703-652fb93fdc2a_903x131.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2c8d825a-e5e4-45bb-9703-652fb93fdc2a_903x131.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2c8d825a-e5e4-45bb-9703-652fb93fdc2a_903x131.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2c8d825a-e5e4-45bb-9703-652fb93fdc2a_903x131.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2c8d825a-e5e4-45bb-9703-652fb93fdc2a_903x131.png" width="903" height="131" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/2c8d825a-e5e4-45bb-9703-652fb93fdc2a_903x131.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:131,&quot;width&quot;:903,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:77608,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2c8d825a-e5e4-45bb-9703-652fb93fdc2a_903x131.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2c8d825a-e5e4-45bb-9703-652fb93fdc2a_903x131.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2c8d825a-e5e4-45bb-9703-652fb93fdc2a_903x131.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2c8d825a-e5e4-45bb-9703-652fb93fdc2a_903x131.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div></div></div></a></figure></div><p>As for the sellers themselves, as <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/dilipvamanan/overlay/about-this-profile/">Dilip Vamanan</a> from SellerApp explained to me, they can be categorised in four main buckets:</p><blockquote><p><em>1. Major FMCG/CPG companies like HUL, ITC, Coca Cola, Pepsi, Red Bull etc <br>2. D2C brands like BoAt, Mamaearth, Bombay Shaving Company, Atomberg etc<br>3. Social sector sellers including Farmer Producer Organizations (FPOs), indigenous craftsman, artisanal producers etc (made up of entities that have largely never sold anything online)<br>4. Retailers and physical stores</em></p></blockquote><p>Much of the seller experience on ONDC so far can be filtered through this lens. For instance when it comes to:</p><ol><li><p><strong>Onboarding time</strong>: For merchants that already have well-maintained digital catalogues (eg: restaurants that are already selling on Swiggy/Zomato), they can be onboarded to the network in 2-4 weeks (one seller app mentioned that it could even be done in an afternoon in the case of digitally native brands). For entities that have primarily offline operations (eg: a small kirana store) or unstandardised products (eg: a local flower vendor) it could take much longer to get them ONDC-ready. Without some technical assistance from an existing seller app or TSP, I&#8217;ve heard that it has even turned into a months-long slog for some network participants. </p></li><li><p><strong>Cataloguing and Inventory Management</strong> - From the feedback I received, this is basically what the quality of the current ONDC experience hinges on. If the cataloguing and inventory management is done accurately and in a timely manner, the sellers tend to have a better experience which translates into happier final users. The challenge pertains to the nuances of cataloguing and inventory management for different sectors and products, along with the need to devote resources to this activity (time, manpower, software etc) even though the current level of demand doesn&#8217;t necessarily justify it.<br>- <strong>eg:</strong> a 100g pack of Parle-g will have a standard description, but 100g of unbranded atta might have large variations in quality, 100g of onions might have a different price every day of the week, and so on.<br>- <strong>eg2</strong>: a tiny juice vendor joining the network needs to update his inventory if he has run out of sugarcane for the day, but this is a new (and crucial) habit that is likely to be more effort than it is worth right now. It means that a buyer looking to order sugarcane juice would place an order for a product that isn&#8217;t in stock, leading to dissatisfaction.</p></li><li><p><strong>Generating orders</strong> - The overall retail order volume on the network is still relatively insignificant (but it&#8217;s <a href="https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/technology/in-january-ondc-racked-up-100000-retail-purchases-every-day-on-average-12193161.html">ticking up already this year</a>). Based on conversations with seller apps and brands, so far the early winners have been DTC products that already have brand recognition (<em>&#8220;getting double digit orders per day right after signing up&#8221;</em>) and to a lesser extent the artisan and social sector, which is able to cater to national demand for the first time. For newer products and lesser-known items, much of the early activity has been incentive-led.</p></li></ol><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F96f77455-8043-4708-b7a6-1a0106a709e1_1441x1439.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F96f77455-8043-4708-b7a6-1a0106a709e1_1441x1439.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F96f77455-8043-4708-b7a6-1a0106a709e1_1441x1439.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F96f77455-8043-4708-b7a6-1a0106a709e1_1441x1439.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F96f77455-8043-4708-b7a6-1a0106a709e1_1441x1439.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F96f77455-8043-4708-b7a6-1a0106a709e1_1441x1439.png" width="1441" height="1439" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/96f77455-8043-4708-b7a6-1a0106a709e1_1441x1439.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1439,&quot;width&quot;:1441,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:2449831,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F96f77455-8043-4708-b7a6-1a0106a709e1_1441x1439.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F96f77455-8043-4708-b7a6-1a0106a709e1_1441x1439.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F96f77455-8043-4708-b7a6-1a0106a709e1_1441x1439.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F96f77455-8043-4708-b7a6-1a0106a709e1_1441x1439.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">The ONDC <a href="https://twitter.com/ONDC_Official">Twitter</a> and <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/open-network-for-digital-commerce?originalSubdomain=in">LinkedIn</a> feeds do a great job of highlighting the performance and arrival of sellers on the network</figcaption></figure></div><p>All this to say, the real audience of ONDC buyers and sellers has yet to be red-pilled. There are only a literal handful of buyer apps that are live on the network (which mainly cater to digitally savvy users). These are the users that won&#8217;t feel the immediate benefits of ONDC to their lives. On the seller side many of the early movers are mature brands and companies that want to experiment with a new channel of distribution. The undigitised mass of sellers is yet to be stirred.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb2f87e39-000f-496b-b2bd-97252bbcdc58_800x1000.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb2f87e39-000f-496b-b2bd-97252bbcdc58_800x1000.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb2f87e39-000f-496b-b2bd-97252bbcdc58_800x1000.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb2f87e39-000f-496b-b2bd-97252bbcdc58_800x1000.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb2f87e39-000f-496b-b2bd-97252bbcdc58_800x1000.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb2f87e39-000f-496b-b2bd-97252bbcdc58_800x1000.jpeg" width="538" height="672.5" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/b2f87e39-000f-496b-b2bd-97252bbcdc58_800x1000.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1000,&quot;width&quot;:800,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:538,&quot;bytes&quot;:144164,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb2f87e39-000f-496b-b2bd-97252bbcdc58_800x1000.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb2f87e39-000f-496b-b2bd-97252bbcdc58_800x1000.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb2f87e39-000f-496b-b2bd-97252bbcdc58_800x1000.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb2f87e39-000f-496b-b2bd-97252bbcdc58_800x1000.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>That&#8217;s why stakeholder education will be a big part of the agenda this year, both for the ONDC organisation, as well as existing buyer and seller apps. In order to scale the network in 2024, content dispersal in different languages, contexts, constituencies will be key&#8230;starting with the first national ONDC ad campaign that was launched in January.</p><div id="youtube2-YsaHgfb3vog" class="youtube-wrap" data-attrs="{&quot;videoId&quot;:&quot;YsaHgfb3vog&quot;,&quot;startTime&quot;:null,&quot;endTime&quot;:null}" data-component-name="Youtube2ToDOM"><div class="youtube-inner"><iframe src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/YsaHgfb3vog?rel=0&amp;autoplay=0&amp;showinfo=0&amp;enablejsapi=0" frameborder="0" loading="lazy" gesture="media" allow="autoplay; fullscreen" allowautoplay="true" allowfullscreen="true" width="728" height="409"></iframe></div></div><p>The good news is that the ONDC flywheel is up and running. There is a natural incentive for sellers of all kinds to continue to join the network and hope it succeeds - what seller doesn&#8217;t want to find a way to reach more customers cheaply while paying less fees to middlemen? And on the buyer side, customers will continue to try ONDC if they can save on the price of goods and services in the short term. Ultimately it will need to offer buyers a better experience and better choices for e-commerce than they have now. That&#8217;s how ONDC wins.</p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://tigerfeathers.substack.com/p/ondc-remixing-commerce?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:&quot;button-wrapper&quot;}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary button-wrapper" href="https://tigerfeathers.substack.com/p/ondc-remixing-commerce?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share"><span>Share</span></a></p><h2>Sweet. So what&#8217;s left to solve?</h2><p>A lot. Like, a lot. Like, basically everything.</p><p>There is far more unsolved than solved. There are huge gaps to fill just to get the ONDC experience to <em>meet</em> the current standard of e-commerce, much less surpass it. In some ways the last two years have been a proof of concept for ONDC. You could even argue that the current version of the ONDC protocol is just the Minimum Viable Product (MVP), and the real development will take place over the coming months and years.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F43315bdb-96c6-4042-928c-39c16c02e2fc_1302x974.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F43315bdb-96c6-4042-928c-39c16c02e2fc_1302x974.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F43315bdb-96c6-4042-928c-39c16c02e2fc_1302x974.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F43315bdb-96c6-4042-928c-39c16c02e2fc_1302x974.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F43315bdb-96c6-4042-928c-39c16c02e2fc_1302x974.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F43315bdb-96c6-4042-928c-39c16c02e2fc_1302x974.png" width="494" height="369.55145929339477" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/43315bdb-96c6-4042-928c-39c16c02e2fc_1302x974.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:974,&quot;width&quot;:1302,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:494,&quot;bytes&quot;:1512915,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F43315bdb-96c6-4042-928c-39c16c02e2fc_1302x974.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F43315bdb-96c6-4042-928c-39c16c02e2fc_1302x974.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F43315bdb-96c6-4042-928c-39c16c02e2fc_1302x974.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F43315bdb-96c6-4042-928c-39c16c02e2fc_1302x974.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>This is evidenced by the ongoing <a href="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/gadgets-news/ondc-announces-build-for-bharat-initiative-for-startups-prizes-and-more/articleshow/105734001.cms?ref=ondc.org">ONDC &#8216;Build for Bharat&#8217; hackathon</a>, which kicked off in December last year. The hackathon invites participants to solve some of the most <a href="https://hack2skill.com/build-for-bharat-hackathon-ondc-google-cloud#problemStatement">pressing unanswered questions</a> about ONDC, including:</p><ul><li><p>creating a seamless experience to manage product returns (i.e. reverse logistics)</p></li><li><p>designing a dynamic cataloguing solution that can help a seller digitise their inventory in under four hours</p></li><li><p>finding a way to inject personalisation and customisation in the customer journey (to reduce drop-off rates) in a manner that protects data privacy</p></li><li><p>designing a peer-to-peer lending ecosystem tailored specifically for agricultural micro-entrepreneurs</p></li><li><p>building a price optimisation engine for sellers (particularly for grocery)</p></li><li><p>using <a href="https://tigerfeathers.substack.com/p/are-we-there-yet">open source maps</a> to tackle various e-commerce functionalities cheaply and effectively</p></li><li><p>creating an embedded solution that allows participants to negotiate directly over the network</p></li><li><p>and much more</p></li></ul><p>That&#8217;s why, if you&#8217;re convinced that ONDC has legs, the opportunities presented by this new paradigm aren&#8217;t restricted to just buyer apps, seller apps, sellers, or logistics players. There is a near endless list of problems worth solving - for old companies and new.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F308b7c1c-0057-41c6-a666-2e5e99113179_998x529.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F308b7c1c-0057-41c6-a666-2e5e99113179_998x529.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F308b7c1c-0057-41c6-a666-2e5e99113179_998x529.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F308b7c1c-0057-41c6-a666-2e5e99113179_998x529.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F308b7c1c-0057-41c6-a666-2e5e99113179_998x529.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F308b7c1c-0057-41c6-a666-2e5e99113179_998x529.png" width="998" height="529" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/308b7c1c-0057-41c6-a666-2e5e99113179_998x529.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:529,&quot;width&quot;:998,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:135095,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2F