?"><span>Subscribe now</span></a></p><h2>Okay, I&#8217;m on board. What now?</h2><p>Now we attempt to finish this off with our version of a rapid fire session.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1475b4db-c308-4b51-affe-a3b557992be6_1822x1025.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1475b4db-c308-4b51-affe-a3b557992be6_1822x1025.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1475b4db-c308-4b51-affe-a3b557992be6_1822x1025.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1475b4db-c308-4b51-affe-a3b557992be6_1822x1025.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1475b4db-c308-4b51-affe-a3b557992be6_1822x1025.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1475b4db-c308-4b51-affe-a3b557992be6_1822x1025.png" width="1456" height="819" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/1475b4db-c308-4b51-affe-a3b557992be6_1822x1025.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:819,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:1506054,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1475b4db-c308-4b51-affe-a3b557992be6_1822x1025.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1475b4db-c308-4b51-affe-a3b557992be6_1822x1025.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1475b4db-c308-4b51-affe-a3b557992be6_1822x1025.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1475b4db-c308-4b51-affe-a3b557992be6_1822x1025.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Tea with Tigerfeathers?</figcaption></figure></div><p>If you&#8217;ve made it all the way here, you&#8217;re probably sick of me. So am I. So instead of doing a neat and tidy exposition of various ONDC mental models, I&#8217;m going to do a quick and dirty collection of Neural Noodles - i.e. strands of thought to pull on with regards to ONDC. This is a ramen bowl of ideas, challenges, opportunities and frameworks that will round off my thinking on ONDC.</p><p>So, without further do (but really after far too much ado), to me, ONDC is like:</p><h3>1. Steph Curry</h3><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F59840fe1-26bf-445b-92e3-6c5afbad1267_715x480.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F59840fe1-26bf-445b-92e3-6c5afbad1267_715x480.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F59840fe1-26bf-445b-92e3-6c5afbad1267_715x480.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F59840fe1-26bf-445b-92e3-6c5afbad1267_715x480.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F59840fe1-26bf-445b-92e3-6c5afbad1267_715x480.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F59840fe1-26bf-445b-92e3-6c5afbad1267_715x480.png" width="647" height="434.34965034965035" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/59840fe1-26bf-445b-92e3-6c5afbad1267_715x480.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:480,&quot;width&quot;:715,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:647,&quot;bytes&quot;:727154,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F59840fe1-26bf-445b-92e3-6c5afbad1267_715x480.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F59840fe1-26bf-445b-92e3-6c5afbad1267_715x480.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F59840fe1-26bf-445b-92e3-6c5afbad1267_715x480.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F59840fe1-26bf-445b-92e3-6c5afbad1267_715x480.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>Steph Curry is the greatest shooter of a basketball that&#8217;s ever walked the Earth. He&#8217;s a triple threat - easy with the lay-up, automatic from mid-range, and lethal from long-distance. </p><p>ONDC&#8217;s impact will be felt at three levels:</p><ul><li><p>The network hopes to &#8216;activate&#8217; the millions of offline kirana stores and micro enterprises across the country, helping to stimulating hyperlocal economies. It could lead to thousands of quick-commerce equivalent services courtesy of local cornershops instead of platform-operated dark stores from the likes of Zepto, Blinkit, and Instamart. </p></li><li><p>It will give local brands access to a national market (and even build new brands around local craftsmanship, local produce, local talent etc)</p></li><li><p>If Beckn continues to make inroads outside of India, it means that Indian sellers will be visible to foreign buying apps on the same network, and Indian buyers will be able to import both raw materials and finished products going the other way (To illustrate - Proxtera, SignCatch, and Rapidor piloted the <a href="https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/economy/ondc-forays-in-b2b-exports-proxtera-comes-onboard-as-international-buyer-app/article67306901.ece">first ever international B2B transaction</a> on ONDC last year).</p></li></ul><h3>2. Mini Cheesecakes</h3><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1fa6754b-f0d7-4148-b50b-e972904fb695_1200x800.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1fa6754b-f0d7-4148-b50b-e972904fb695_1200x800.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1fa6754b-f0d7-4148-b50b-e972904fb695_1200x800.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1fa6754b-f0d7-4148-b50b-e972904fb695_1200x800.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1fa6754b-f0d7-4148-b50b-e972904fb695_1200x800.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1fa6754b-f0d7-4148-b50b-e972904fb695_1200x800.jpeg" width="630" height="420" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/1fa6754b-f0d7-4148-b50b-e972904fb695_1200x800.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:800,&quot;width&quot;:1200,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:630,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;Mini Cheesecake Recipe - Saving Room for Dessert&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Mini Cheesecake Recipe - Saving Room for Dessert&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="Mini Cheesecake Recipe - Saving Room for Dessert" title="Mini Cheesecake Recipe - Saving Room for Dessert" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1fa6754b-f0d7-4148-b50b-e972904fb695_1200x800.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1fa6754b-f0d7-4148-b50b-e972904fb695_1200x800.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1fa6754b-f0d7-4148-b50b-e972904fb695_1200x800.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1fa6754b-f0d7-4148-b50b-e972904fb695_1200x800.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>The base layer is the same but the toppings are all different. For ONDC, each segment, each category, each geography, each micro-ecosystem will require a nuanced approach to achieve adoption at scale. Those tweaks will need to be made both at the protocol level as well as on the operational side. ONDC needs entrepreneurs and service providers to go deep, instead of broad, to address the specific demands and challenges of different products and supply chains.</p><p>Eg: Electronics will need a embedded insurance flow to give people the comfort to buy high value products on ONDC</p><p>Eg2: Fashion will need logistics arrangement for returning clothes that don&#8217;t fit</p><p>This is the biggest contrast when it comes to comparing the implementation of UPI vs ONDC. UPI had only one SKU - money. It was easy to standardise the workflow because it was just one digital &#8216;product&#8217; being moved across the (payment) rails. ONDC has millions of physical products and services that have significant differences in how they are purchased, serviced, and delivered.</p><p>A one-cheesecake-fits-all approach on ONDC will not work. This will necessitate a diverse set of technological and logistical solutions that will need to be implemented (e.g: buyer apps in local languages, delivery via bicycles, modifications for different categories at the protocol level etc), while also opening the door for millions of small business to find success as e-commerce enablers instead of a market dominated by a handful of giant platforms.</p><h3>3. Sgt. Pepper&#8217;s Lonely Hearts Club Band</h3><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb7ddb11c-1189-4687-8df1-3428b7051545_1372x772.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb7ddb11c-1189-4687-8df1-3428b7051545_1372x772.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb7ddb11c-1189-4687-8df1-3428b7051545_1372x772.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb7ddb11c-1189-4687-8df1-3428b7051545_1372x772.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb7ddb11c-1189-4687-8df1-3428b7051545_1372x772.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb7ddb11c-1189-4687-8df1-3428b7051545_1372x772.png" width="686" height="386" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/b7ddb11c-1189-4687-8df1-3428b7051545_1372x772.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:772,&quot;width&quot;:1372,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:686,&quot;bytes&quot;:2175323,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb7ddb11c-1189-4687-8df1-3428b7051545_1372x772.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb7ddb11c-1189-4687-8df1-3428b7051545_1372x772.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb7ddb11c-1189-4687-8df1-3428b7051545_1372x772.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb7ddb11c-1189-4687-8df1-3428b7051545_1372x772.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p><em>A Day in the Life - </em>perhaps the greatest song from the greatest album of all time? It&#8217;s certainly in the conversation.</p><p>Rahul Handa, the EVP of Strategic Initiatives at ONDC, says that, beyond the quantitative results, you have to look at the impact of ONDC in the context of &#8220;a day in the life&#8221; of someone living in a part of India that has yet to be lit up by e-commerce.</p><p>In a post-ONDC landscape, what would it mean for hundreds of millions of individuals and entrepreneurs across the country to be able to suddenly buy and sell things online?</p><p>Maybe a shopkeeper in rural Punjab doesn&#8217;t need to travel to the nearest city to sell his surplus harvest?</p><p>Maybe the home delivery of emergency medical supplies can reduce the number of preventable deaths in remote parts of India?</p><p>Maybe a mother of three from Choravane can reallocate the hours spent travelling to and from the local <em>mandi</em>?</p><p>These things can&#8217;t be accounted for in seller commissions or TAM figures. Much like UPI, ONDC is a social construct as much as it is an economic construct. When assessing the need and effectiveness of a DPI approach to digital commerce, it&#8217;s important not to leave the human-side unaccounted for.</p><h3>4. The Ajna Chakra (&#8220;The Third Eye&#8221;)</h3><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F071394f6-c024-4744-b155-205ac4207f70_2930x2020.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F071394f6-c024-4744-b155-205ac4207f70_2930x2020.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F071394f6-c024-4744-b155-205ac4207f70_2930x2020.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F071394f6-c024-4744-b155-205ac4207f70_2930x2020.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F071394f6-c024-4744-b155-205ac4207f70_2930x2020.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F071394f6-c024-4744-b155-205ac4207f70_2930x2020.jpeg" width="620" height="427.5274725274725" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/071394f6-c024-4744-b155-205ac4207f70_2930x2020.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1004,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:620,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;A Guide to Understanding the Chakra System: The Third Eye Chakra&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;A Guide to Understanding the Chakra System: The Third Eye Chakra&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="A Guide to Understanding the Chakra System: The Third Eye Chakra" title="A Guide to Understanding the Chakra System: The Third Eye Chakra" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F071394f6-c024-4744-b155-205ac4207f70_2930x2020.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F071394f6-c024-4744-b155-205ac4207f70_2930x2020.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F071394f6-c024-4744-b155-205ac4207f70_2930x2020.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F071394f6-c024-4744-b155-205ac4207f70_2930x2020.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Source: Aura Camera</figcaption></figure></div><p>On one hand, ONDC blurs the line between online and offline. For instance, retailers and physical stores that join ONDC will be able to display their previously physical inventory in a digital storefront i.e. offline becomes online.</p><p>On the other hand, ONDC is a new channel entirely - a third channel - like opening the e-commerce equivalent of The Ajna Chakra. </p><p>So brands will now almost have to think of three separate strategies for:<br>1. Offline distribution (via kirana stores, retail chains, supermarkets etc); <br>2. E-commerce (via marketplaces, and their own websites and Direct-To-Consumer channels); and<br>3. ONDC (where a single integration with a seller app gives them a footprint in every relevant buyer app on the network).</p><p>This could have a number of downstream consequences that will only make themselves apparent over time.</p><p>For example, a prominent DTC brand selling on the network told me that ONDC might necessitate a rethink when it comes to retail promotion strategy. Large &#8216;distribution-first&#8217; brands often keep separate SKUs for offline and online distribution. For instance, an electronics brand might have a specific model/colour of headphones only available offline and not online (to incentivise an offline retailer like Chroma to carry and promote their brand). If all physical catalogues suddenly become digital via ONDC, it could cause conflicts in the omni-channel promotional strategies of consumer brands.</p><p>The owner of a QSR restaurant chain I interviewed (that had recently joined the network) mentioned that, while he was still apprehensive about the prospects of ONDC, he was hopeful that just the mere presence of an alternative e-commerce channel would be beneficial to his economics (<em>&#8220;The best case scenario is that Swiggy and Zomato are forced to lower their commission rates to compete with ONDC. That solves all my problems. Swiggy&#8217;s logistics network is not just great, it&#8217;s reliable. I don&#8217;t have to take any tension on the delivery side. Ideally I want to continue using them. So if ONDC pushes these guys to cut their fees then that would be the best of both worlds&#8221;</em>).</p><p>Perhaps the biggest clues about the utility of ONDC as the key to unlocking a new commercial medium can be found in the actions and responses of the leading FMCG brands in India. For instance:</p><ul><li><p>Last year <a href="https://www.medianama.com/2023/04/223-itc-ondc-anonymised-data-sharing-framework/">ITC proposed</a> that if ONDC could share anonymised data with its participants it would help to make supply chains across the country more efficient (because brands like them could concentrate their stocks at retailers in the localities that saw a lot of online ordering on ONDC)</p></li><li><p>Coca Cola - through its <a href="https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/coca-cola-join-ondc-launches-marketplace-coke-shop/article67569308.ece">&#8216;Coke Shop&#8217;</a> - is helping its retail partners sell via ONDC, so consumers have more touch-points to buy the company&#8217;s products. Mondelez International has <a href="https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/mondelez-explores-partnership-with-ondc/article66230923.ece">the same idea</a>.</p></li><li><p>Marico is integrating its <a href="https://www.livemint.com/companies/news/marico-partners-ondc-for-saffola-store-11687768524119.html">&#8216;Saffola Store&#8217;</a> Direct-To-Consumer platform with ONDC to explore &#8216;new avenues for growth, collaboration, and enhanced digital experiences&#8217;.</p></li><li><p>Hindustan Unilever (HUL) <a href="https://www.etnownews.com/companies/hindustan-unilever-striding-ahead-heres-what-the-company-said-on-future-growth-financial-performance-and-demand-trends-article-100607355">earlier experimented</a> with integrating its own DTC platform &#8216;U-Shop&#8217; with the network. It is now extending its <a href="https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/services/retail/hul-to-help-kiranas-compete-with-bigger-players-via-ondc/articleshow/105192446.cms?from=mdr">internal ordering tool &#8216;Shikhar&#8217; with ONDC</a>, effectively allowing the 1.3 million kirana stores that order directly from the company to sell online via ONDC (even allowing these kiranas to make sales of products that are from HUL&#8217;s competitors). This would allow HUL to <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/aartinyayadhish_hindustan-unilever-to-help-kirana-stores-activity-7130841933861572608-z2o-/">get a sense</a> of their share of kirana inventory and online wallet spend.</p></li></ul><blockquote><p><em>&#8220;Digitisation has democratised India and I know ONDC is going to democratise digi-commerce.&#8221;</em><br><strong>- <a href="https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/business/ondc-will-democratise-digi-commerce-e-com-is-huls-fastest-growing-channel-rohit-jawa-12235691.html">Rohit Jawa</a> (MD &amp; CEO at HUL)</strong></p></blockquote><p>These gigantic companies are primarily &#8216;distribution-led&#8217;, meaning they have deeply entrenched supply chains and webs of channel partners (wholesalers, distributors, retailers) to distribute their various products. While they are extremely active and effective at marketing their brands, the ultimate sale is usually made either by an offline retailer or an online marketplace. ONDC helps them exert more control over their digital activities, helping to accelerate a part of their outreach strategy that has so far been relatively untapped.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb4233447-d57c-4583-838c-02ea5cf0f051_1330x660.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb4233447-d57c-4583-838c-02ea5cf0f051_1330x660.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb4233447-d57c-4583-838c-02ea5cf0f051_1330x660.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb4233447-d57c-4583-838c-02ea5cf0f051_1330x660.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb4233447-d57c-4583-838c-02ea5cf0f051_1330x660.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_2400,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb4233447-d57c-4583-838c-02ea5cf0f051_1330x660.png" width="1126" height="558.7669172932331" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/b4233447-d57c-4583-838c-02ea5cf0f051_1330x660.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:false,&quot;imageSize&quot;:&quot;large&quot;,&quot;height&quot;:660,&quot;width&quot;:1330,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:1126,&quot;bytes&quot;:392637,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-large" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb4233447-d57c-4583-838c-02ea5cf0f051_1330x660.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb4233447-d57c-4583-838c-02ea5cf0f051_1330x660.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb4233447-d57c-4583-838c-02ea5cf0f051_1330x660.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb4233447-d57c-4583-838c-02ea5cf0f051_1330x660.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">from the <a href="https://blume.vc/reports/indus-valley-annual-report-2023">Indus Valley Annual Report 2023</a> by Blume VC</figcaption></figure></div><p>The CPG/FMCG angle came up in almost every conversation I had as the likely first area where ONDC could genuinely shake up the status quo. Among several benefits, ONDC gives these companies:</p><ul><li><p>a way to <em>see</em> their final customers directly for the first time, instead of doing it through the dense tangle of their supply chains (eg: they can design promotional campaigns directly with buyer apps and precisely measure the responses/sales/performance)</p></li><li><p>an online channel to sell products with different features and economics (eg: low-margin high-volume SKUs like shampoo sachets)</p></li><li><p>a way to extend their reach even further and deeper in the country via local buyer apps that will hopefully bring a new legion of customers onto the network in the medium-to-long term</p></li></ul><p>And from an ONDC perspective, by bringing their supply chains onto the network, these companies could catalyse a circular economy of B2B buying and selling on ONDC. Watch this space.</p><h3>5. The Galapagos Islands</h3><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F30c33e90-ce94-490e-8bbc-ac576e0d7ceb_1200x800.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F30c33e90-ce94-490e-8bbc-ac576e0d7ceb_1200x800.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F30c33e90-ce94-490e-8bbc-ac576e0d7ceb_1200x800.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F30c33e90-ce94-490e-8bbc-ac576e0d7ceb_1200x800.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F30c33e90-ce94-490e-8bbc-ac576e0d7ceb_1200x800.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F30c33e90-ce94-490e-8bbc-ac576e0d7ceb_1200x800.jpeg" width="642" height="428" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/30c33e90-ce94-490e-8bbc-ac576e0d7ceb_1200x800.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:800,&quot;width&quot;:1200,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:642,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;The waters of the Galapagos Islands are being invaded by alien species |  New Scientist&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;The waters of the Galapagos Islands are being invaded by alien species |  New Scientist&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="The waters of the Galapagos Islands are being invaded by alien species |  New Scientist" title="The waters of the Galapagos Islands are being invaded by alien species |  New Scientist" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F30c33e90-ce94-490e-8bbc-ac576e0d7ceb_1200x800.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F30c33e90-ce94-490e-8bbc-ac576e0d7ceb_1200x800.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F30c33e90-ce94-490e-8bbc-ac576e0d7ceb_1200x800.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F30c33e90-ce94-490e-8bbc-ac576e0d7ceb_1200x800.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Source: New Scientist</figcaption></figure></div><blockquote><p><em>The Gal&#225;pagos Islands, isolated in the Pacific Ocean, boast unparalleled biodiversity, housing unique species found nowhere else in the world. From iconic Galapagos tortoises to flightless cormorants and Godzilla-esque marine iguanas, there is a wealth of unique creatures that have specifically adapted to this environment. Darwin's observations here inspired his theory of evolution by natural selection, underscoring the islands' significance in shaping our understanding of life. The Gal&#225;pagos serve as a living laboratory, showcasing the interplay between species and their surroundings.<br></em><strong>- ChatGPT (give me a break man, I&#8217;m exhausted)</strong></p></blockquote><p>On the ONDC archipelago, don&#8217;t look for the same species of e-commerce participants that you&#8217;re used to seeing everywhere else. That&#8217;s not where the magic will be. The constructs of an open protocol for commerce require inhabitants to undergo specific adaptations to suit their surroundings. You can&#8217;t use linear comparisons to existing products and services to appreciate the potential impact of ONDC. You have to get weird. You have to use Godzilla-vision. You have to think exponential.</p><blockquote><p><em>&#8220;This is as big as the internet. This is difficult to comprehend. People can comprehend linearity &#8211; they cant comprehend non-linear, exponential. It is very very difficult to get exponential. This is why we always underestimate. It is important to understand that non-linearity is going to kick in. And when that kicks in, you will see exponential growth in places that you wouldn&#8217;t even expect.&#8221;</em><br><strong>- <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zwHDzbQl8CA&amp;t=561s&amp;ab_channel=AntlerGlobal">Pramod Varma</a> (Chief Architect of Aadhaar and Co-founder of the Beckn Foundation)&nbsp;</strong></p></blockquote><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd843aa94-d951-4f51-8a60-f74ee2633e28_1999x1225.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd843aa94-d951-4f51-8a60-f74ee2633e28_1999x1225.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd843aa94-d951-4f51-8a60-f74ee2633e28_1999x1225.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd843aa94-d951-4f51-8a60-f74ee2633e28_1999x1225.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd843aa94-d951-4f51-8a60-f74ee2633e28_1999x1225.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_2400,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd843aa94-d951-4f51-8a60-f74ee2633e28_1999x1225.png" width="960" height="588.1318681318681" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/d843aa94-d951-4f51-8a60-f74ee2633e28_1999x1225.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:false,&quot;imageSize&quot;:&quot;large&quot;,&quot;height&quot;:892,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:960,&quot;bytes&quot;:1390971,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-large" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd843aa94-d951-4f51-8a60-f74ee2633e28_1999x1225.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd843aa94-d951-4f51-8a60-f74ee2633e28_1999x1225.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd843aa94-d951-4f51-8a60-f74ee2633e28_1999x1225.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd843aa94-d951-4f51-8a60-f74ee2633e28_1999x1225.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Exponential growth in UPI transactions (upper left); bank accounts linked via Account Aggregators (upper right); second and third-order effects of FASTAG (bottom) [Source: <a href="http://file:///Users/rahul/Downloads/20%20Things%20About%20India's%20Digital%20Public%20Infrastructure%20.pdf">India Quotient</a>]</figcaption></figure></div><p>Like I said in the introduction to this piece (65 million years ago), for ONDC, we&#8217;ve left the primordial ooze stage behind. We are now on the cusp of a Cambrian explosion, and it&#8217;s difficult to predict what kinds of strange species will be spit up by the unique terrain, like:</p><ul><li><p>What kinds of brands, products and startups become economically viable when the cost of acquiring customers goes to zero? What does e-commerce look like in a positive-sum construct instead of a zero-sum competition?</p></li><li><p>What happens to our national supply chain infrastructure if interoperability helps logistics networks to become hyper efficient?</p></li><li><p>What kind of new e-commerce experiences can we unlock via a Beckn-enabled network of networks (e.g - a wedding app that allows you to book a venue, a singer, a dress, and transport from the airport using an AI-assisted budget tracker?; e.g - a B2B marketplace for the steel industry where different players can buy and sell raw materials, recycled waste matter, and finished products at precise points in their manufacturing cycles?; e.g - an entertainment portal for Mumbai where independent writers can upload scripts, production houses can advertise casting vacancies, financiers can offer credit and insurance, and actors can upload their CVs?)</p></li><li><p>What will be the effect on national GDP if we free up the billions of hours currently spent by a majority of the country in the physical act of buying and selling things?</p></li><li><p>What does an e-commerce market without advertising look like? Does it lead to a different class of winning and losing brands? How does that effect marketing budgets or conventional design standards?</p></li><li><p>What happens if the big incumbent platforms - <a href="https://www.livemint.com/companies/news/amazon-to-join-india-s-ondc-network-11677226685771.html">Amazon</a>, Swiggy, <a href="https://www.livemint.com/companies/ola-joins-government-backed-ondc-for-food-delivery-services-report-11693617984829.html">Ola</a>, Bigbasket, Udaan etc - join ONDC? Does it strengthen or weaken ONDC&#8217;s case? Would they plug in via their current marketplaces, or create separate ONDC-lite version of their platforms? Will they replace parts of their current businesses with the ONDC version (similar to how wallet providers pivoted to UPI, or how PayTM already <a href="https://blog.paytmmall.com/paytm-mall-announces-pivot-to-ondc-as-its-primary-focus-e5a3e3ebdc0f">shuttered PayTM</a> mall in favour of ONDC)?</p></li><li><p>What happens if/when our major consumer platforms (fintech apps, social media apps, OTT platforms, health trackers etc) come aboard ONDC as buyer apps? Could plug-and-play e-commerce ever have a meaningful impact on their bottom line? What kind of unique buying experiences could they design?</p></li><li><p>What happens to the financial services industry if a meaningful chunk of India&#8217;s e-commerce moves to ONDC? What can you do with the exhaust fumes of that data? Can millions of kiranas get loans against their sales? Can a street vendor get access to a daily loan?</p></li><li><p>What new e-commerce enablers will we need to make the ONDC model work as envisioned - do we need insurance for product returns? Do we need an instant scan-and-upload device for offline catalogues? Do we need an AI-bot that flags harmful items on the network? Do we need fleets of rural delivery agents? Do we need an India-specific open source maps platform? Do we need a SaaS solution for batching delivery agents across seller apps?</p></li></ul><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F61bdafa9-78ac-41c7-8251-f45d237026b5_1050x700.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F61bdafa9-78ac-41c7-8251-f45d237026b5_1050x700.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F61bdafa9-78ac-41c7-8251-f45d237026b5_1050x700.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F61bdafa9-78ac-41c7-8251-f45d237026b5_1050x700.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F61bdafa9-78ac-41c7-8251-f45d237026b5_1050x700.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F61bdafa9-78ac-41c7-8251-f45d237026b5_1050x700.jpeg" width="1050" height="700" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/61bdafa9-78ac-41c7-8251-f45d237026b5_1050x700.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:700,&quot;width&quot;:1050,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;Adopt a Blue-footed Booby | Symbolic Adoptions from WWF&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Adopt a Blue-footed Booby | Symbolic Adoptions from WWF&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="Adopt a Blue-footed Booby | Symbolic Adoptions from WWF" title="Adopt a Blue-footed Booby | Symbolic Adoptions from WWF" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F61bdafa9-78ac-41c7-8251-f45d237026b5_1050x700.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F61bdafa9-78ac-41c7-8251-f45d237026b5_1050x700.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F61bdafa9-78ac-41c7-8251-f45d237026b5_1050x700.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F61bdafa9-78ac-41c7-8251-f45d237026b5_1050x700.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Like much of the wildlife on the Galapagos - including this <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blue-footed_booby">blue-footed booby</a> pictured above - the species of commercial entities on ONDC will probably look weird and unfamiliar (Source: WWF)</figcaption></figure></div><blockquote><p><em>&#8220;The Internet is a great example of how a new paradigm gets built. At first, people thought it was just a hassle, no real value there. It was like a solution looking for a problem. But then bam! Killer apps like Amazon and ChatGPT came out of nowhere. There is nothing obvious in the design of the internet that could have foretold the form and variety of the new killer apps/breakthrough inventions it would unleash. This begs the question - what is stopping us from imagining newer forms of open internets? The Beckn protocol and ONDC-on-Beckn then become necessary ideas, not just nice ideas.&nbsp;Imagine the future if we can pull this off!&#8221;<br></em><strong>- <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/sujithnairk/?originalSubdomain=in">Sujith Nair</a> (CEO &amp; Co-founder at FIDE | Genesis Co-author &amp; Steward - Beckn Protocol)</strong></p></blockquote><p>Just like how you couldn&#8217;t have predicted that recurring payments on UPI would lead to the <a href="https://tigerfeathers.substack.com/p/a-sonic-bridge-to-indias-heartlands">success of OTT entertainment platforms</a> back in 2016, or the fact that a paper sticker on your car to deduct toll payments would make capital expenditure for national highway construction more viable, it&#8217;s nearly impossible to predict exactly how the market will respond, or what those effects will be. Sometimes you have to just let nature run its course&#128034;.</p><h3>6. The Marshmallow Test</h3><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0953c0e6-ef2a-46e2-b2a2-53cd71ca83cf_830x465.webp" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0953c0e6-ef2a-46e2-b2a2-53cd71ca83cf_830x465.webp 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0953c0e6-ef2a-46e2-b2a2-53cd71ca83cf_830x465.webp 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0953c0e6-ef2a-46e2-b2a2-53cd71ca83cf_830x465.webp 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0953c0e6-ef2a-46e2-b2a2-53cd71ca83cf_830x465.webp 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0953c0e6-ef2a-46e2-b2a2-53cd71ca83cf_830x465.webp" width="610" height="341.7469879518072" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/0953c0e6-ef2a-46e2-b2a2-53cd71ca83cf_830x465.webp&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:465,&quot;width&quot;:830,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:610,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;Image&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Image&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="Image" title="Image" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0953c0e6-ef2a-46e2-b2a2-53cd71ca83cf_830x465.webp 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0953c0e6-ef2a-46e2-b2a2-53cd71ca83cf_830x465.webp 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0953c0e6-ef2a-46e2-b2a2-53cd71ca83cf_830x465.webp 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0953c0e6-ef2a-46e2-b2a2-53cd71ca83cf_830x465.webp 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>The <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stanford_marshmallow_experiment">Marshmallow Test</a> is a psychological experiment assessing children's ability to delay gratification by offering them the choice of a smaller immediate reward (of one marshmallow) or a larger reward (of two marshmallows) if they can wait for a period of time.</p><p>It is an iconic experiment, hailed as the premier yardstick of adolescent self-control, frequently cited as a credible predictor of future success.</p><p>If you tried it on adults today, we&#8217;d all fail miserably.</p><p>We live in the age of instant gratification. Our digital lives (courtesy of our digital platforms) have been geared to make sure that any of our hearts&#8217; desires are met at the click of a button. Within the duration of a long bathroom break, you can get anything from dessert to deodorant delivered to the doorstep of your house.</p><p>It&#8217;s why it&#8217;s been so tough to make a case for the ONDC version of grocery, food delivery, and household items - at least for users living in Tier-1 cities. Currently the average ONDC experience is a tiny bit worse than what we&#8217;re used to, and without the generous incentive programme it would be hard to make a case for why you&#8217;d log into ONDC vs any of your existing favourite apps.</p><p>However, 75% of India&#8217;s digital population (~600-700 million people) isn&#8217;t used to that level of digital service just yet.</p><blockquote><p><em>&#8220;&#8230;when you talk about Ranchi and Bhubaneswar and the fact that there are no Instamart and Zepto equivalents, it always brings us back to this problem of India - 3,000 square km of India thinks that the 3 million square km of India is the<br>same.&#8221;<br></em><strong>- <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=709&amp;v=pYQd4wjUPVs&amp;embeds_referring_euri=https%3A%2F%2Fyoutubetranscript.com%2F&amp;source_ve_path=MzY4NDIsMzY4NDIsMzY4NDIsMzY4NDIsMzY4NDIsMjM4NTE&amp;feature=emb_title">Susmit Patodia</a> (Antler India)</strong></p></blockquote><p>So to find opportunities where ONDC might represent a genuine improvement on the status quo, a couple of useful questions to ask might be:</p><ul><li><p>What experiences do we take for granted in Tier-1 India that, if delivered at even 50% efficacy in Tier-4 India, would lead to a material difference in the quality of life for hundreds of millions of people?</p></li><li><p>For the class of digital &#8216;superusers&#8217; living in metropolitan cities, what e-commerce experience, product, or service would we be willing to forgo instant gratification for in exchange for a new ONDC-enabled benefit?</p></li><li><p>Which digital experience is currently broken, or does not have a deeply entrenched incumbent?</p></li></ul><h3>7. Chai</h3><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5dff676c-9b97-4d4f-a0bd-df99dc422a12_830x465.webp" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5dff676c-9b97-4d4f-a0bd-df99dc422a12_830x465.webp 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5dff676c-9b97-4d4f-a0bd-df99dc422a12_830x465.webp 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5dff676c-9b97-4d4f-a0bd-df99dc422a12_830x465.webp 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5dff676c-9b97-4d4f-a0bd-df99dc422a12_830x465.webp 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5dff676c-9b97-4d4f-a0bd-df99dc422a12_830x465.webp" width="592" height="331.66265060240966" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/5dff676c-9b97-4d4f-a0bd-df99dc422a12_830x465.webp&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:465,&quot;width&quot;:830,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:592,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;Image&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Image&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="Image" title="Image" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5dff676c-9b97-4d4f-a0bd-df99dc422a12_830x465.webp 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5dff676c-9b97-4d4f-a0bd-df99dc422a12_830x465.webp 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5dff676c-9b97-4d4f-a0bd-df99dc422a12_830x465.webp 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5dff676c-9b97-4d4f-a0bd-df99dc422a12_830x465.webp 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>Another one borrowed from <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=1084&amp;v=2kwJbb706ew&amp;embeds_referring_euri=https%3A%2F%2Fyoutubetranscript.com%2F&amp;source_ve_path=MzY4NDIsMzY4NDIsMzY4NDIsMzY4NDIsMzY4NDIsMzY4NDIsMzY4NDIsMzY4NDIsMzY4NDIsMjM4NTE&amp;feature=emb_title">Rahul Handa</a> that ties into the previous point:</p><blockquote><p><em>&#8220;There'll be a certain set of people who will walk into a hotel - into a five-star hotel - and pay 500 rupees for a tea. There will be another set of people who will go to a smaller restaurant or hotel and pay 200 rupees. There's also another set of people who will go down to the local tapri on the street and order a 5 and 10 rupee tea.</em></p><p><em>Now, the services that are involved along with that price point also change. So, that means that [for] the customer, whatever they are expecting is going to be dependent on the price point also.</em></p><p><em>&#8230;There will be more options for customers to buy products and services that they are used to buying in the physical world. And in the digital world more and more sellers will be able to get on and sell their products at the price point etc that they require without having to worry about margins and terms and conditions and when will they get paid etc etc.</em></p></blockquote><p>India is a study in contradictions. <em>Indians</em>, are not a homogenous mass of people. When your starting point is 1.5 billion people living in a land mass of 3.3 million sq km, you will get people with different preferences, problems, capabilities, and lifestyles.</p><p>Everyone doesn&#8217;t need or want the same types of products and services. Yet, for the most part, the first era of e-commerce in India has focused on the requirements of a tiny sliver of the population - the cream of the consuming class. And that makes sense. If you&#8217;re trying to make money as a platform, you want to be catering to customers that are happy to trade their disposable income in exchange for convenience.</p><p>However, with ONDC changing the economics of e-commerce, there&#8217;s an opportunity now to cater to customers that are open to making different kinds of trade-offs.&nbsp;</p><p>Unlike the &#8220;avocado economy&#8221; that will typically trade money for convenience (like the people that will go to a five star hotel for chai), other segments of our population might be more willing to trade time for access (e.g.: ordering a pair of spectacles online even if they take two weeks to arrive), or time for money (e.g.: joining a skills based portal on ONDC to find gig work).</p><p>An important question to be answered in the coming years will be to figure out what e-commerce mechanisms, schemes and arrangements will provide &#8216;India 2&#8217; and &#8216;India 3&#8217; customers with the trust, cost, convenience, and comfort to buy and sell things online.</p><h3>8. This thing</h3><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F32b1f0ab-aac3-4c75-bfd6-6cbfe52bc503_830x465.webp" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F32b1f0ab-aac3-4c75-bfd6-6cbfe52bc503_830x465.webp 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F32b1f0ab-aac3-4c75-bfd6-6cbfe52bc503_830x465.webp 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F32b1f0ab-aac3-4c75-bfd6-6cbfe52bc503_830x465.webp 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F32b1f0ab-aac3-4c75-bfd6-6cbfe52bc503_830x465.webp 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F32b1f0ab-aac3-4c75-bfd6-6cbfe52bc503_830x465.webp" width="658" height="368.6385542168675" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/32b1f0ab-aac3-4c75-bfd6-6cbfe52bc503_830x465.webp&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:465,&quot;width&quot;:830,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:658,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;Image&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Image&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="Image" title="Image" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F32b1f0ab-aac3-4c75-bfd6-6cbfe52bc503_830x465.webp 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F32b1f0ab-aac3-4c75-bfd6-6cbfe52bc503_830x465.webp 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F32b1f0ab-aac3-4c75-bfd6-6cbfe52bc503_830x465.webp 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F32b1f0ab-aac3-4c75-bfd6-6cbfe52bc503_830x465.webp 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>ONDC is about activating the long tail.</p><p>It&#8217;s not about you and me.</p><p>If ONDC <em>does</em> manage to steal market share away from Amazon, Uber, Zomato, Instamart and others in the big metros (on its own merit, not its juicy discounts) - that&#8217;s a bonus. But that&#8217;s not really the main goal here.</p><p>Instead, ONDC is really about the edges, the niches, the fat pockets. It&#8217;s about the buyers and sellers and products and ecosystems that, for whatever reason, have been left in the shadow of India&#8217;s marketplace monoliths. Each of these (relatively) small segments added up together make up the ~75% and ~94% of Indian consumers and businesses that aren&#8217;t currently buying and selling things online, respectively.</p><p>In fact, you could probably boil down the ONDC value proposition to a single hypothesis, which states that, <strong>the major reason these people and businesses aren&#8217;t participating in e-commerce is because of the limitations of the centralised marketplace model</strong>. In the interest of objectivity, there remains a non-zero probability that this hypothesis turns out to be false, but it&#8217;ll take a few years to validate that claim one way or the other.</p><p>In any case, on the bright side, if you choose to operate on the assumption that that is indeed the case, it means that there will be a treasure trove of opportunities to take digital commerce to people and places in India that haven&#8217;t been exposed to it yet. To capture the long tail, it&#8217;s worth asking questions like:</p><ul><li><p>Where could you stimulate digital demand where it hasn&#8217;t been stimulated yet?</p></li><li><p>What vibrant micro-ecosystems could benefit from offline physical activity moving online?</p></li><li><p>What product or service is there not a marketplace for yet, but clear demand and an abundance of sellers?</p></li></ul><p>The benefit for ONDC sellers is that they can source demand hyperlocally, nationally and (eventually) internationally, all from the same network, and essentially immediately after coming on board. The value proposition is self-evident. We could see niche seller apps that specifically aim to onboard:<br>- Tanjore painters from Bihar<br>- Street food vendors from South Mumbai<br>- Home chefs in Chennai<br>- Graphic designers from Indiranagar<br>- Tea farmers from Munnar, etc</p><p>There will be a requirement for a corresponding suite of niche enabling services for each of these groups that takes into account the demands of local supply chains, local languages, different categories and sectors, different demographics and economic conditions etc. </p><p>The unbundling of the network makes this doubly potent.</p><p>It&#8217;s usually the demand side of the marketplace equation that is expensive to assimilate. Given that ONDC takes this burden off the shoulders of sellers and seller apps, coupled with the fact that logistics costs will be handled by third parties, means that suddenly you could have a large number of viable small businesses built around various seller onboarding and seller services applications.&nbsp;</p><p>The biggest contrast when it comes to ONDC vs the legacy platform model, is that platforms were programmed to optimise for scale. The unbundled, decentralised nature of an open network means that network particpants on ONDC could find greater success optimising for focus. ONDC might not conceive as many unicorns as UPI did, but it could very well surpass it for the number of regular, capable stallions in the stable.</p><h3>9. Bubble tea</h3><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd78ced0-318a-4226-8782-f165a4816479_830x465.webp" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd78ced0-318a-4226-8782-f165a4816479_830x465.webp 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd78ced0-318a-4226-8782-f165a4816479_830x465.webp 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd78ced0-318a-4226-8782-f165a4816479_830x465.webp 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd78ced0-318a-4226-8782-f165a4816479_830x465.webp 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd78ced0-318a-4226-8782-f165a4816479_830x465.webp" width="618" height="346.2289156626506" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/bd78ced0-318a-4226-8782-f165a4816479_830x465.webp&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:465,&quot;width&quot;:830,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:618,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;Image&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Image&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="Image" title="Image" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd78ced0-318a-4226-8782-f165a4816479_830x465.webp 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd78ced0-318a-4226-8782-f165a4816479_830x465.webp 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd78ced0-318a-4226-8782-f165a4816479_830x465.webp 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbd78ced0-318a-4226-8782-f165a4816479_830x465.webp 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>Bubble tea was a popular local drink in Taiwan in the 1980s. It probably tasted weird AF to anyone not from Taiwan. But Taiwanese immigrants brought it to the United States in the 1990s, kickstarting its popularity in the West. And once the rainbow colours of Bubble tea collided with the filter-friendly panels of Instagram, <em>boba</em> became a global phenomenon. It became fashionable.</p><p>ONDC might seem weird, niche and perhaps even unnecessary to some people now. You could argue that at this very moment it is at peak unpopularity i.e. it is unfashionable. But one day it might not be. Just like UPI.</p><p>UPI was launched by the RBI in April 2016, and was doing just 100k transactions per month in October of that year (vs more than 10 billion per month now). You could argue that it was demonetisation that accelerated the pace of adoption, or COVID that made people more dependent on digital payments.&nbsp;</p><p>Or you could take another school of thought.&nbsp;</p><p>The road to 10 billion transactions would not have happened if UPI hadn&#8217;t become <em>fashionable</em>. This manifested in it becoming totally normal to say &#8216;just Gpay me bro&#8217;. Or it was the gradual prevalence of QR codes in our surroundings, accepted at every retail operation from jewellery stores to coconut vendors. No one blinks now when you ask if &#8220;UPI <em>chalega?&#8221;</em>, and in fact merchants that don&#8217;t accept UPI are likely to receive quizzical looks from their customers (because how can you not accept UPI today <em>bhai sahab</em>?!)</p><p>The philosopher John Locke said in the 17th century that if you want to change how people behave, don&#8217;t change laws, change fashion. (I couldn&#8217;t verify that statement myself but Anthony Bourdain mentioned it in one of his <a href="https://www.google.com/search?q=anthony+bourdain+last+interview+john+locke&amp;sca_esv=c24955e436027d1c&amp;rlz=1C5CHFA_enIN926IN926&amp;sxsrf=ACQVn0_ATYtm_tJ6_Oy2LR-IZBAGoAicVg%3A1708032894250&amp;ei=foPOZbfvDqOq4-EPs-CFgAg&amp;ved=0ahUKEwi3prSvpq6EAxUj1TgGHTNwAYAQ4dUDCBA&amp;uact=5&amp;oq=anthony+bourdain+last+interview+john+locke&amp;gs_lp=Egxnd3Mtd2l6LXNlcnAiKmFudGhvbnkgYm91cmRhaW4gbGFzdCBpbnRlcnZpZXcgam9obiBsb2NrZTIHECEYChigATIHECEYChigATIHECEYChigAUjnH1CXCliHH3ABeAGQAQCYAeEEoAHuGKoBCzAuMi4xLjEuMC40uAEDyAEA-AEBwgIKEAAYRxjWBBiwA8ICBBAjGCfCAgYQABgWGB7CAgUQIRigAYgGAZAGAw&amp;sclient=gws-wiz-serp">last ever interviews</a>, and that&#8217;s good enough for me).</p><p>It doesn&#8217;t matter how many statements are made by the Ministry of Commerce or ONDC leadership extolling the virtues of open networks or digital commerce. We probably won&#8217;t see real adoption till it&#8217;s fashionable to use ONDC, till it isn&#8217;t seen as sub-standard or low-brow or low-tech (at least for the digitally privileged).</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb397d5f5-e34d-4295-b0ba-1e1f0cfe280e_939x468.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb397d5f5-e34d-4295-b0ba-1e1f0cfe280e_939x468.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb397d5f5-e34d-4295-b0ba-1e1f0cfe280e_939x468.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb397d5f5-e34d-4295-b0ba-1e1f0cfe280e_939x468.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb397d5f5-e34d-4295-b0ba-1e1f0cfe280e_939x468.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb397d5f5-e34d-4295-b0ba-1e1f0cfe280e_939x468.png" width="592" height="295.0543130990415" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/b397d5f5-e34d-4295-b0ba-1e1f0cfe280e_939x468.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:468,&quot;width&quot;:939,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:592,&quot;bytes&quot;:930361,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb397d5f5-e34d-4295-b0ba-1e1f0cfe280e_939x468.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb397d5f5-e34d-4295-b0ba-1e1f0cfe280e_939x468.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb397d5f5-e34d-4295-b0ba-1e1f0cfe280e_939x468.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb397d5f5-e34d-4295-b0ba-1e1f0cfe280e_939x468.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Source: <a href="https://yourstory.com/2023/08/antler-ondc-founders-startups-nandan-nilekani-beckn-protocol-ecommerce">Yourstory</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>Maybe that&#8217;s influencers on Instagram instructing their fans to buy their products from an ONDC enabled buyer app. Maybe that&#8217;s popular renegade DTC brands shifting their catalogues to ONDC entirely. Maybe it&#8217;s something else. Instead of waiting for the &#8216;QR code&#8217; moment for ONDC, it&#8217;s probably more pertinent to look out for when we cross the &#8216;just Gpay me bro&#8217; chasm.&nbsp;And if you&#8217;re already part of the network and trying to drum up excitement, you need to find a way to make it cool to come onboard.</p><h3>10. Glenn Maxwell</h3><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0c5bd500-7265-4c96-a7c3-8292150fb5e5_360x360.gif" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0c5bd500-7265-4c96-a7c3-8292150fb5e5_360x360.gif 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0c5bd500-7265-4c96-a7c3-8292150fb5e5_360x360.gif 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0c5bd500-7265-4c96-a7c3-8292150fb5e5_360x360.gif 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0c5bd500-7265-4c96-a7c3-8292150fb5e5_360x360.gif 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0c5bd500-7265-4c96-a7c3-8292150fb5e5_360x360.gif" width="420" height="420" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/0c5bd500-7265-4c96-a7c3-8292150fb5e5_360x360.gif&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:360,&quot;width&quot;:360,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:420,&quot;bytes&quot;:7306063,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/gif&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0c5bd500-7265-4c96-a7c3-8292150fb5e5_360x360.gif 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0c5bd500-7265-4c96-a7c3-8292150fb5e5_360x360.gif 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0c5bd500-7265-4c96-a7c3-8292150fb5e5_360x360.gif 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0c5bd500-7265-4c96-a7c3-8292150fb5e5_360x360.gif 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>Success in ONDC may come down to iterating your way to finding an effective strategy to win within the rules of the game i.e. it&#8217;s about figuring out how to best leverage the upside of the protocol-based approach while being cognizant of where this approach falls short. </p><p>Last year <span class="mention-wrap" data-attrs="{&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Sangeet Paul Choudary&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:3927722,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;user&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:null,&quot;photo_url&quot;:&quot;https://bucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/54a044f6-e037-4f1d-8694-cd4ef885134d_600x400.png&quot;,&quot;uuid&quot;:&quot;0c8ecf77-0aa7-4c4a-a06b-0d02493d533f&quot;}" data-component-name="MentionToDOM"></span>the Founder of Platformation Labs and author of <a href="https://www.amazon.in/Platform-Revolution-Networked-Transforming-Economy/dp/0393249131">Platform Revolution</a>, wrote an excellent blogpost on <a href="https://platforms.substack.com/p/the-ondc-conundrum-where-protocols">&#8216;</a><em><strong><a href="https://platforms.substack.com/p/the-ondc-conundrum-where-protocols">where protocols win</a></strong></em><a href="https://platforms.substack.com/p/the-ondc-conundrum-where-protocols">&#8217;</a>, specifically from the lens of ONDC. Choudary pointed out:<br>- the fallacy of the unbundling + interoperability argument<br>- factors that determine whether protocols win or lose<br>- how to determine which players win and lose in a protocol&#8217;s ecosystem</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0bedb63b-5ac5-41e2-a188-6b63a80706c2_4076x4076.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0bedb63b-5ac5-41e2-a188-6b63a80706c2_4076x4076.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0bedb63b-5ac5-41e2-a188-6b63a80706c2_4076x4076.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0bedb63b-5ac5-41e2-a188-6b63a80706c2_4076x4076.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0bedb63b-5ac5-41e2-a188-6b63a80706c2_4076x4076.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0bedb63b-5ac5-41e2-a188-6b63a80706c2_4076x4076.png" width="668" height="668" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/0bedb63b-5ac5-41e2-a188-6b63a80706c2_4076x4076.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1456,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:668,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0bedb63b-5ac5-41e2-a188-6b63a80706c2_4076x4076.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0bedb63b-5ac5-41e2-a188-6b63a80706c2_4076x4076.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0bedb63b-5ac5-41e2-a188-6b63a80706c2_4076x4076.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0bedb63b-5ac5-41e2-a188-6b63a80706c2_4076x4076.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Source: <a href="https://platforms.substack.com/p/the-ondc-conundrum-where-protocols">Platform Revolution</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>The entire piece is worth reading in its entirety. But to highlight his three &#8216;laws of protocol economics&#8217; encapsulated in the graph above:</p><ul><li><p><em><strong>A protocol creates value through unbundling to the extent that it can absorb and resolve the coordination costs originating from unbundling.</strong></em></p></li><li><p><em><strong>The more the number of steps in the value chain you unbundle, the higher the coordination costs.</strong></em></p></li><li><p><em><strong>A protocol&#8217;s ability to absorb coordination costs is inversely proportional to the degree of variability in use cases it needs to directly coordinate.</strong></em></p></li></ul><p>Effectively, he warned that despite UPI and ONDC both being protocol-based solutions, the higher degree of complexity, numerous steps in the supply chain, and variability of use cases on ONDC mean that protocol-based digital commerce might not have the same success as protocol-based digital payments.</p><p>Based on this:</p><blockquote><p><em>&#8220;&#8230;there are two key factors that determine ONDC&#8217;s effectiveness as a protocol-based open network:</em></p><ol><li><p><em>Resolving coordination costs in the ecosystem by fostering at-scale, vertically integrated players at and across activities where coordination costs are too high.</em></p></li><li><p><em>Focusing on categories that support differentiated inventory, support margins high enough to absorb coordination costs, and ideally benefit from local network effects.&#8221;</em></p></li></ol><p><em><strong>Managing protocols is not just a question of where/what you decentralize.</strong></em></p><p><em><strong>It is as much (or even more so) a question of where/what you centralize&#8221;.</strong></em></p></blockquote><p>It is a useful heuristic to use when deciding how to tackle ONDC. It is also worth pointing out that Choudary concludes his piece by saying that even if ONDC loses the battle to &#8216;decentralize and unseat large players in commerce&#8217;, it can still win by &#8216;onboarding offline sellers and democratising access to their inventory&#8217;. Only time will tell.</p><h3>11. Lego</h3><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0fcc8514-2db2-444e-987b-89617d256ade_830x465.webp" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0fcc8514-2db2-444e-987b-89617d256ade_830x465.webp 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0fcc8514-2db2-444e-987b-89617d256ade_830x465.webp 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0fcc8514-2db2-444e-987b-89617d256ade_830x465.webp 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0fcc8514-2db2-444e-987b-89617d256ade_830x465.webp 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0fcc8514-2db2-444e-987b-89617d256ade_830x465.webp" width="618" height="346.2289156626506" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/0fcc8514-2db2-444e-987b-89617d256ade_830x465.webp&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:465,&quot;width&quot;:830,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:618,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;Image&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Image&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="Image" title="Image" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0fcc8514-2db2-444e-987b-89617d256ade_830x465.webp 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0fcc8514-2db2-444e-987b-89617d256ade_830x465.webp 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0fcc8514-2db2-444e-987b-89617d256ade_830x465.webp 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0fcc8514-2db2-444e-987b-89617d256ade_830x465.webp 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><blockquote><p><em>&#8220;It&#8217;s just like the physical world where different building blocks of the value chain are built by different players. Think of the auto industry. Does a single automaker manufacture everything from tyres to engines to seats? They don&#8217;t. They outsource the components and then assemble everything together. That&#8217;s exactly what we are doing for ecommerce.&#8221;</em><br><strong>- <a href="https://www.forbesindia.com/article/take-one-big-story-of-the-day/ondc-is-indias-next-big-bet-after-upi/85073/1">T. Koshy</a> (CEO - ONDC)</strong></p></blockquote><p>We finish this the way we started, with Lego. You see, modern commerce is assembled not built. Even the incumbent marketplaces we use on a regular basis lean on a number of third parties to fill in crucial functions in the value chain.</p><p>Sometimes this takes the form of a bilateral relationship with a logistics partner, or an API arrangement with a SaaS provider for customer service or recommendations or to facilitate payments. It is rare that one party will ever have the expertise to handle everything. Maybe they can develop those capabilities over time (like Amazon), but more likelier than not a typical e-commerce transaction involves the coming together of a number of different puzzle pieces.</p><p>ONDC just takes that to the extreme. It leaves things to the market, trusting a protocol to orchestrate all the various moving parts (in real time) instead of just one (vertically integrated) company. This approach expands the surface area for more specialist players to contribute - to provide cataloguing solutions, to create voice-assisted user interfaces, or AI-assisted shopping cart construction.</p><p>So ONDC is not that much of a departure from the way things are currently set up. It is in the vein of &#8216;same-same, but different&#8217;.</p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://tigerfeathers.substack.com/p/ondc-remixing-commerce?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:&quot;button-wrapper&quot;}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary button-wrapper" href="https://tigerfeathers.substack.com/p/ondc-remixing-commerce?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share"><span>Share</span></a></p><div><hr></div><p>ONDC is a wildly ambitious never-been-done-before project to see if we can figure out a different way to make the digital economy work for the most number of people. When all is said and counted, there may be a thousand different reasons for why it fails. It would be a shame if one of those reasons was a failure of imagination. So it might be trivial to dismiss many of the claims of ONDC to be untrue, but, to take a leaf out of the page of the immortal <a href="https://www.newyorker.com/books/page-turner/the-two-friends-who-changed-how-we-think-about-how-we-think">Amos Tversky</a>, it is far more interesting to &#8220;ask what it might be true <em>of</em>&#8221;.</p><h2>Word. </h2><p>Yeah.</p><h2>Right, anyway, let&#8217;s bring this one home?</h2><p>Sure, and for that we briefly return to where this piece began (many words and lifetimes ago) - Mumbai.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1b542d14-8c13-4c75-8c21-ee2820744179_1200x600.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1b542d14-8c13-4c75-8c21-ee2820744179_1200x600.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1b542d14-8c13-4c75-8c21-ee2820744179_1200x600.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1b542d14-8c13-4c75-8c21-ee2820744179_1200x600.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1b542d14-8c13-4c75-8c21-ee2820744179_1200x600.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1b542d14-8c13-4c75-8c21-ee2820744179_1200x600.jpeg" width="1200" height="600" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/1b542d14-8c13-4c75-8c21-ee2820744179_1200x600.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:600,&quot;width&quot;:1200,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;Failure of Mumbai's Monorail Holds Lessons for Urban Planners Everywhere&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Failure of Mumbai's Monorail Holds Lessons for Urban Planners Everywhere&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="Failure of Mumbai's Monorail Holds Lessons for Urban Planners Everywhere" title="Failure of Mumbai's Monorail Holds Lessons for Urban Planners Everywhere" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1b542d14-8c13-4c75-8c21-ee2820744179_1200x600.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1b542d14-8c13-4c75-8c21-ee2820744179_1200x600.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1b542d14-8c13-4c75-8c21-ee2820744179_1200x600.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1b542d14-8c13-4c75-8c21-ee2820744179_1200x600.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Source: The Wire</figcaption></figure></div><p>Back in 2014, India&#8217;s commercial capital was cheering on the arrival of a different hunk of shiny steel - the iconic and ill-fated Mumbai Monorail. It is the first (and remains to date) the only monorail system in India. In a city as cosmopolitan as Mumbai, the one thing that people from all walks of life can agree on is that the Monorail has been an unmitigated disaster.</p><blockquote><p><em>&#8220;Experts had warned even then that it was a foolhardy idea, which would have no practical or substantive impact on the city&#8217;s transportation since monorail rakes have low carrying capacity, the planned route is unnecessary and expensive and the technology untested &#8211; it hasn&#8217;t been used as a mode of mass transportation anywhere in the world &#8211; and will have low cost-recovery rate&#8221;.<br></em><strong>- Guru Kamble (<a href="https://thewire.in/urban/failure-of-mumbais-monorail-holds-lessons-for-urban-planners-everywhere">The Wire, 2019</a>)</strong></p></blockquote><p>Back in 2005, it was originally envisioned as a saviour to Mumbai&#8217;s overflowing public transport systems (ring a bell?). The hope was that - with its nimble design and ability to make sharp, snaking turns - the Monorail would take some of the load off of Mumbai&#8217;s suburban rail network (which ferries ~7.5 million Mumbaikars everyday), and act as a feeder system to our other public transport services.</p><p>Considering that it currently boasts a paltry daily ridership between <a href="https://www.hindustantimes.com/cities/mumbai-news/mumbais-monorail-becomes-a-financial-burden-with-expected-losses-of-529-crore-101692386686003.html">9,000-10,000</a>, it has achieved neither.</p><p>Why? Because it&#8217;s been plagued by an entire menu&#8217;s worth of calamities right from the design stage up to the actual implementation. To whit, the Monorail route passes through a mostly marshy Eastern corridor of Mumbai with no shops, offices or residential areas around. Its stations aren&#8217;t really close to any other bus stops or train stations (meaning it actually adds more time to someone&#8217;s commute instead of reducing it). It&#8217;s suffered permission delays, mechanical failures, rake fires, changes in route alignment - you name it. Add to that the fact that wait times can stretch to over 30 minutes, it&#8217;s not hard to see why it&#8217;s become a &#8377;3000 crore white elephant since being opened to the public ten years ago.</p><p>The only people who&#8217;ve benefitted are the tourists that use it for weekend joyrides, and the real estate developers who pre-sold residential land on the anticipation of the Monorail&#8217;s impact on Mumbai&#8217;s East side.</p><h2>For the last time, how is that relevant here?</h2><p>The Mumbai Monorail is a stark reminder that when it comes to the success of large public works projects, just because it looks good on paper doesn&#8217;t mean it&#8217;ll look good in reality. Just because you&#8217;ve been successful at identifying the problem, doesn&#8217;t mean you&#8217;ll be successful at identifying the solution. A plan to tackle a problem isn&#8217;t worth much if the design, implementation and adoption come up short. </p><p>If we return to our analogy of ONDC as an infinite digital mall in cyberspace, the failure of the Monorail actually contains a number of useful lessons on how to think about navigating the next few years of ONDC.</p><p>If all goes well with this digital mall, there will be plenty of opportunities to go around - for store owners, for marketers, for financiers, for road builders, for parking lot operators etc. But to make it a success, plenty of groundwork needs to be done to make sure that the electricity works, that it&#8217;s easy to access, that it&#8217;s clean, that there&#8217;s security, that the right brands have a spot, that there&#8217;s enough footfall, that the cool kids show up. All the necessary ingredients need to fall in place to give ONDC a chance to succeed. There is no divine press-button-for-commerce solution that can be called upon here.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff4298c50-18da-4d9d-9a0f-426af8157db3_1204x895.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff4298c50-18da-4d9d-9a0f-426af8157db3_1204x895.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff4298c50-18da-4d9d-9a0f-426af8157db3_1204x895.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff4298c50-18da-4d9d-9a0f-426af8157db3_1204x895.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff4298c50-18da-4d9d-9a0f-426af8157db3_1204x895.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff4298c50-18da-4d9d-9a0f-426af8157db3_1204x895.png" width="560" height="416.27906976744185" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/f4298c50-18da-4d9d-9a0f-426af8157db3_1204x895.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:895,&quot;width&quot;:1204,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:560,&quot;bytes&quot;:1493454,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff4298c50-18da-4d9d-9a0f-426af8157db3_1204x895.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff4298c50-18da-4d9d-9a0f-426af8157db3_1204x895.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff4298c50-18da-4d9d-9a0f-426af8157db3_1204x895.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff4298c50-18da-4d9d-9a0f-426af8157db3_1204x895.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">It doesn&#8217;t work that way.</figcaption></figure></div><p>What we do know is that:</p><ul><li><p>The DPI approach has a stellar track record for supercharging digital inclusion</p></li><li><p>In India we&#8217;ve chosen to bet on open networks instead of closed platforms (and that bet has paid off)</p></li><li><p>Public building blocks can be melted into rocket fuel for private innovation</p></li><li><p>Orchestrating the movement of atoms will be infinitely harder than orchestrating the movement of bits</p></li></ul><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3e0eb031-ddcb-4b75-9d90-06a2b20c8caf_977x273.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3e0eb031-ddcb-4b75-9d90-06a2b20c8caf_977x273.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3e0eb031-ddcb-4b75-9d90-06a2b20c8caf_977x273.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3e0eb031-ddcb-4b75-9d90-06a2b20c8caf_977x273.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3e0eb031-ddcb-4b75-9d90-06a2b20c8caf_977x273.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_2400,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3e0eb031-ddcb-4b75-9d90-06a2b20c8caf_977x273.png" width="846" height="236.39508700102354" data-attrs="{&quot;src&