MF</p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.internetgovernance.org/wp-content/uploads/India_stack_9_1_2023.pdf?_gl=1*rj3qeu*_up*MQ..*_ga*NDM1NTM1MjQ2LjE2OTM1NTQxOTI.*_ga_BN246XV4L5*MTY5MzU1NDE5MC4xLjAuMTY5MzU1NDE5MC4wLjAuMA..">India Stack: Public-Private Roads to Data Sovereignty</a> by the Internet Governance Project</p></li><li><p><a href="https://hbr.org/2023/05/the-case-for-investing-in-digital-public-infrastructure">The Case for Investing in Digital Public Infrastructure</a> by Harvard Business Review</p></li><li><p><a href="http://file:///Users/rahul/Downloads/20%20Things%20About%20India's%20Digital%20Public%20Infrastructure%20.pdf">20 Things About India&#8217;s Digital Public Infrastructure</a> by India Quotient</p></li><li><p><a href="https://research.ispirt.in/articles/Designing-Digital-Public-Goods#Unified_payment">Designing Digital Public Goods and Playgrounds in India: The Need for Theoretical and Contextual Analysis</a> by Arun Mohan Sukumar (iSpirt)</p></li><li><p><a href="https://blume.vc/commentaries/india-b2bs-next-big-opportunity-crossborder-commerce">India B2B's next big opportunity: Crossborder commerce</a> by Blume VC</p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.bain.com/insights/how-india-shops-online-2023/#:~:text=India's%20e%2Dretail%20market%20is,was%20driven%20by%20inflationary%20pressures.">How India Shops Online</a> by Bain &amp; Company</p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.bain.com/globalassets/noindex/2022/bain_report-the_rise_of_digital_bazaars_in_india.pdf">The Rise of Digital Bazaars in India</a> by Bain &amp; Company</p></li></ul><div><hr></div><h4>ACKNOWLEDGEMENTS</h4><p>I owe a massive thank you to several individuals who took the time out to chat with me and share their insights for this story. This includes Akhil Jayaprakash (Pulse Energy), Rajan Mehra (Nirvana Venture Advisors), Susmit Patodia (Antler India), Sujith Nair (Beckn), Hrushikesh Mehta (ONDC), Anvita Khosla (Kalaari Capital), Girish Pai (GrowthFalcons), Puranika Narayana Bhatta (LatLong), Shayak Mazumder (Adya.ai), Pradeep KP (Dhiway), Rahul Mathur (InsuranceDekho), Dilip Vamanan (SellerApp), Himanshu Dikshit, Raj Desai (SOAL), Aarti Nyayadhish (eSamudaay), Mandeep Julka (Chiratae Ventures), Manoj Gupta (Plotch.ai), Snehith Budime (DailyBee), Anirudh Ganesh (Hotelzify), Faiz Mohammed (FIDE), Rahul Handa (ONDC), Vivek Lohcheb (Pincode), Sooryah Pokkali (Bitsila), Sumit Duggal (SignCatch), Kapish Kaushal (ONDC), Nilesh Vasita (UniStack), Rishi Talwar (Accenture), Sangeet Paul Choudary (Platformation Labs), and several others who have opted to remain uncredited, but to whom I am indebted to for the generosity with their knowledge and time.</p><p>A huge shoutout to my co-conspirator at Tigerfeathers - Aaryaman Vir - for contributing to the technical exposition in this piece, and particularly for bringing the Beckn section to life.</p><p>And finally, a big thank you to Antler India for supporting our efforts. I&#8217;ve gotten to know and admire several members of their team over the years. This is technically the first official partnership we&#8217;ve ever done at Tigerfeathers, so I&#8217;ll always be grateful to them for deeming our logo worthy of standing next to theirs.</p><div><hr></div><p><strong>If you made it all the way here and you thought this was a good use of your time, it would mean a lot to us if you took a couple of seconds to share this post.</strong></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://tigerfeathers.substack.com/p/globetrotters-1-bank-on-juno?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share&amp;token=eyJ1c2VyX2lkIjo5OTYxNjg4LCJwb3N0X2lkIjo3NDM4NDA5OCwiaWF0IjoxNjc5MzE2NzczLCJleHAiOjE2ODE5MDg3NzMsImlzcyI6InB1Yi01OTIxOCIsInN1YiI6InBvc3QtcmVhY3Rpb24ifQ.7rVdDgcg8zbj_HfsduWlKxqyNIcCgwfvWaV2PNlWzAc&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:&quot;button-wrapper&quot;}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button prim